&lt;p&gt;At Squarespace, we empower millions of creators—from artists to entrepreneurs—to build a brand and transact with their customers through a beautiful and reliable online presence. For every one of these customers, that journey begins with a domain—and we call it &lt;em&gt;Dream it. Domain it.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Domains product team owns the full domain lifecycle, from purchase and setup to management, renewals, and long-term portfolio health. Our goal is to deliver an intuitive, secure, and high-quality experience that supports customers at every level of domain knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Registrar Operations Lead&lt;/strong&gt;, you will play a critical role in ensuring operational excellence across our domains business. You will serve as a senior escalation owner and interface across&amp;nbsp; Customer Support, Engineering, Legal, Security, ICANN, registries, and external partners, helping resolve complex domain issues with rigor, judgment, and a strong focus on compliance, security and customer impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is designed for a senior domain professional who combines deep industry expertise with hands-on operational and technical capability. You will be trusted to independently investigate and resolve complex issues, partner closely with Engineering to reduce manual workflows through tooling and automation, and represent Squarespace with confidence in external registry and policy-facing interactions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report directly to the Domain Registrar Operations leader and may work remotely (U.S) or in a hybrid role at our NYC headquarters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Get To… &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Escalations &amp;amp; Tech Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the senior escalation owner for complex, high-impact domain-related customer issues, working closely with Customer Support, Security and Engineering to ensure timely, accurate resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply hands-on expertise across gTLDs and ccTLDs, high-value and expired domain workflows, DNS, EPP, REST APIs, and registry platforms to investigate and resolve issues directly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform root-cause analysis on issues, and provide clear guidance and recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert and advisor to internal teams on domain-related cases, workflows, and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UDRP, Compliance &amp;amp; Legal Collaboration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the internal expert on UDRP cases, and registry compliance matters, partnering closely with Legal and external registries to manage disputes and enforcement actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a deep understanding of ICANN policies and regulations, including ICANN RAA, GDPR, and abuse-related requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and support compliance initiatives to ensure registrar operations align with evolving policy and contractual obligations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Abuse &amp;amp; Security Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with internal Security and Trust teams on domain abuse identification, escalation, and mitigation efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define and improve operational processes related to DNS abuse handling, reporting, and registry coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
